cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the application of deep learning algorithms for medical image classification, specifically for diabetic retinopathy from funduscopic images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a semi-supervised learning approach, which involves the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs), which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of GANs for medical image classification also falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of the learning process, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
